   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The current sensor should be installed at a point with the full
battery current that is going to a Reality system, unit in a redundant
Reality system or other system. The current sensor housing can be attached
to a DIN rail 35 x 7.5 mm (TS35 rail).</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">If multiple current sensors are used, configure a unique address
with the DIP switches on each current sensor connected to the same
webmanager.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">It is recommended to connect the current sensor to a battery bus
(COM3) port on the webmanager with a BACS bus cable.<note class="- topic/note ">The maximum
bus cable length between the current sensor and the webmanager is
10 m (32 ft). For more information see <xref href="GBMS_Bus_Cable_Length_and_Wiring_Details_CPT_0000511676.dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="concept"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</note>If a sensormanager is
used, it is also possible to connect the current sensor to the sensormanager
with RJ12 cables.</p>
